# fastcodon.aio — P32/P33: the async layer built ON the callback reactor.
#
# Public API (import from fastcodon.aio.streams / fastcodon.aio.timeout):
#   streams: Stream, Completion, Continuation, wrap_stream, connect_stream
#   timeout: Timeout, TimeoutAction, after
#
# Design: there is no async/await; an operation returns a `Completion` result-holder that the
# reactor fills, and callers attach a `Continuation` object (virtual dispatch, since Codon
# closures don't unify to one callable type — same idiom as the reactor's IOHandler).
